<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="19" pageNumber="174" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,150,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Description</emphasis>
: Coloration. General body color light brown (
<figureCitation box="[859,991,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-106@17.[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.,: 66. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 67. Female, habitus, dorsal view; 68. Male head, anterior view; 69. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 70. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 66–67 = 1mm; 68–69 = 0.3mm; 70 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405039/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Figs 66–67</figureCitation>
). Lateral carinae of the frons above lateral ocelli, apical half of the clypeus, vertex, median region of pronotum and mesonotum yellow. Forewing: basal half light brown and apical half with several small whitish and brown areas: long, white diffuse band in the middle portion of postcostal cell extending to until the icua cross-vein; white, diffuse spot at apex of postcostal extending to the sc-r cross-vein; C1 and C1’ cells predominantly white; apical half of the C2 cell white; white rounded spot at apex of cells C2 ‘, C3a, C3a”, C3’ and C3b; big white longitudinal spot inside cell C3; C4’ cell predominantly white; small white spot on the apex of the clavus (
<figureCitation box="[707,805,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 126–133. Wings of Bennarella species. 126. Bennarella bicoloripennis Muir; 127. Bennarella fusca Muir; 128. Bennarella guidai sp. nov.; 129. Bennarella henriquesi sp. nov.; 130. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.; 131. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.; 132. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.; 133. Bennarella xavieri sp. nov.. Abbreviations: A1, first anal vein; A2, second anal vein; CuA1; CuA2; CuP, Cubitus posterior; MP1, first media posterior branch; MP2, second media posterior branch; MP3, third media posterior branch; MP4, fourth media posterior branch; MP5, fifth media posterior branch; Pcu+A1, Postcubitus+first anal vein; Pcu, Postcubitus; RA, radius anterior branch; RP1, first radius posterior branch; RP2, second radius posterior branch; ScP, Subcosta posterior. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405067/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Fig. 130</figureCitation>
). Pterostigma yellow. Hindwing hyaline, brown. Foreleg and mid leg dark brown, hind leg yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[726,810,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-106@17.[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.,: 66. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 67. Female, habitus, dorsal view; 68. Male head, anterior view; 69. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 70. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 66–67 = 1mm; 68–69 = 0.3mm; 70 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405039/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
). Abdomen dark brown, except upper half of sternite III, dorsal region of sternite IV and V yellow; anal tube, pygofer and genital style yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1359,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-106@17.[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.,: 66. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 67. Female, habitus, dorsal view; 68. Male head, anterior view; 69. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 70. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 66–67 = 1mm; 68–69 = 0.3mm; 70 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405039/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Figs 66, 70</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">
Head: frons with median carina present but weakly marked; lateral carina of frons weakly directed obliquely laterally (
<figureCitation box="[260,346,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-106@17.[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.,: 66. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 67. Female, habitus, dorsal view; 68. Male head, anterior view; 69. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 70. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 66–67 = 1mm; 68–69 = 0.3mm; 70 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405039/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
); vertex length approximately half the median length of the pronotum in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1423,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-106@17.[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.,: 66. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 67. Female, habitus, dorsal view; 68. Male head, anterior view; 69. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 70. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 66–67 = 1mm; 68–69 = 0.3mm; 70 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405039/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
); pedicel approximately 4 times longer than wide and scape conspicuous in anterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1245,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-106@17.[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.,: 66. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 67. Female, habitus, dorsal view; 68. Male head, anterior view; 69. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 70. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 66–67 = 1mm; 68–69 = 0.3mm; 70 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405039/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
). Thorax: pronotum with median longitudinal carina absent; mesonotum with median and lateral longitudinal carinae present and strongly marked (
<figureCitation box="[348,432,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-106@17.[151,1435,380,1852]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.,: 66. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 67. Female, habitus, dorsal view; 68. Male head, anterior view; 69. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 70. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 66–67 = 1mm; 68–69 = 0.3mm; 70 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405039/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Forewing: m-cu cross-vein present (
<figureCitation box="[854,952,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 126–133. Wings of Bennarella species. 126. Bennarella bicoloripennis Muir; 127. Bennarella fusca Muir; 128. Bennarella guidai sp. nov.; 129. Bennarella henriquesi sp. nov.; 130. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.; 131. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.; 132. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.; 133. Bennarella xavieri sp. nov.. Abbreviations: A1, first anal vein; A2, second anal vein; CuA1; CuA2; CuP, Cubitus posterior; MP1, first media posterior branch; MP2, second media posterior branch; MP3, third media posterior branch; MP4, fourth media posterior branch; MP5, fifth media posterior branch; Pcu+A1, Postcubitus+first anal vein; Pcu, Postcubitus; RA, radius anterior branch; RP1, first radius posterior branch; RP2, second radius posterior branch; ScP, Subcosta posterior. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405067/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">Fig. 130</figureCitation>
). Legs: hind tibia with 6 apical spines; hind tarsus with 8+7 apical spines.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405045" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6405045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="174" startId="19.[151,264,1846,1870]" targetBox="[151,1435,711,1822]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1846,1977]" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,341,1846,1870]" pageId="19" pageNumber="174">FIGURES 78–83.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Viegas &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2022" authorityName="Viegas &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2022" box="[348,603,1846,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Bennarella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculipennis" status="sp. nov.">
