</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,409,798,825]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Viegas &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2022" authorityName="Viegas &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2022" box="[419,701,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Bennarella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculipennis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[419,701,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Bennarella maculipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[711,804,799,825]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[711,804,799,825]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is a distinctive species and differs from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muir" authorityYear="1930" box="[233,356,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Bennarella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[233,356,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Bennarella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by forewing with m-cu cross-vein present, forewing with small white spots on apical half, male terminalia with anal tube straight with long base and apex smoothly reentrant, two spines on periandrium and on aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
